## Installation Summary

### 1. Created a Dedicated Wazuh VM

A new Ubuntu Server VM was created in Proxmox with:

```text
4 CPU cores
6GB RAM
80GB disk
VirtIO network adapter
Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS
```

---

### 2. Installed Wazuh

Wazuh was installed using the official all-in-one deployment method.

```bash
curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.14/wazuh-install.sh
sudo bash wazuh-install.sh -a
```

After installation, the Wazuh dashboard became accessible at:

```text
https://192.168.1.25
```

---

### 3. Deployed a Wazuh Agent

A Wazuh agent was installed on the Ubuntu LXC running Grafana and Prometheus.

The agent was deployed from the Wazuh dashboard using:

```text
Deploy new agent
Linux
DEB amd64
Server address: 192.168.1.25
Agent name: grafana-prometheus
```

After installation, the agent appeared as active in the Wazuh dashboard.

