## Docker Monitoring Configuration

The monitored Ubuntu LXC was running Docker containers for:

```text
Grafana
Prometheus
Node Exporter
Uptime Kuma
```

The Docker listener was enabled in the Wazuh agent configuration file:

```bash
/var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf
```

The following block was added before the closing `</ossec_config>` tag:

```xml
<wodle name="docker-listener">
  <disabled>no</disabled>
  <interval>10m</interval>
  <attempts>5</attempts>
  <run_on_start>yes</run_on_start>
</wodle>
```

The Wazuh agent was then restarted:

```bash
systemctl restart wazuh-agent
```

The Wazuh agent logs confirmed that the Docker listener started successfully:

```text
Module docker-listener started.
Starting to listening Docker events.
```

Docker event visibility in the Wazuh dashboard still requires further testing and validation.

