## Challenges Faced

### Prometheus Was Running in Docker

Initially, I attempted to restart Prometheus using:

```bash
systemctl restart prometheus
```

This failed because Prometheus was not installed as a native Linux service. It was running inside Docker.

The correct command was:

```bash
docker restart prometheus
```

This helped reinforce the difference between:

```text
systemd services
Docker containers
SIEM log visibility
```

---

### Docker Events Required Additional Configuration

Wazuh detected Linux system activity immediately, such as user creation, package installation, and sudo activity.

Docker activity required the Docker listener to be enabled manually in the Wazuh agent configuration.

The listener successfully started, but Docker event visibility in the dashboard still needs further testing.

